<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="404" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[113,700,1055,1519]" pageId="1" pageNumber="404">
Otamanho diminuto e a forma coleopteróide devem contribuir para a baixa representatividade desta família nas coleções. Foi reconhecida como subfamília de 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[279,428,1144,1167]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pentatomidae</taxonomicName>
por 
<bibRefCitation author="McATEE, W. L. &amp; J. R. MALLOCH" journalOrPublisher="Proc. U. S. Natl. Mus." pageId="1" pageNumber="404" pagination="1 - 21" part="72" refId="ref3810" refString="McATEE, W. L. &amp; J. R. MALLOCH 1928. Sinopsis of pentatomid bugs of the subfamilies Megaridinae and Canopinae. Proc. U. S. Natl. Mus. 72 (25): 1 - 21." title="Sinopsis of pentatomid bugs of the subfamilies Megaridinae and Canopinae" type="journal article" year="1928">McAtee &amp; Malloch (1928)</bibRefCitation>
e elevada à família por 
<bibRefCitation author="McDONALD, F. J. D." box="[450,634,1174,1197]" journalOrPublisher="J. New York Entomol. Soc." pageId="1" pageNumber="404" pagination="42 - 54" part="87" refId="ref3895" refString="McDONALD, F. J. D. 1979. A new species of Megaris and the status of the Megarididae McAtee &amp; Malloch and Canopidae Amyot &amp; Serville (Hemiptera: Pentatomoidea). J. New York Entomol. Soc. 87 (1): 42 - 54." title="A new species of Megaris and the status of the Megarididae McAtee &amp; Malloch and Canopidae Amyot &amp; Serville (Hemiptera: Pentatomoidea)" type="journal article" year="1979">McDonald (1979)</bibRefCitation>
. Estudando a genitália de ambos os sexos, 
<bibRefCitation author="McDONALD, F. J. D." box="[521,699,1203,1226]" journalOrPublisher="J. New York Entomol. Soc." pageId="1" pageNumber="404" pagination="42 - 54" part="87" refId="ref3895" refString="McDONALD, F. J. D. 1979. A new species of Megaris and the status of the Megarididae McAtee &amp; Malloch and Canopidae Amyot &amp; Serville (Hemiptera: Pentatomoidea). J. New York Entomol. Soc. 87 (1): 42 - 54." title="A new species of Megaris and the status of the Megarididae McAtee &amp; Malloch and Canopidae Amyot &amp; Serville (Hemiptera: Pentatomoidea)" type="journal article" year="1979">McDonald (1979)</bibRefCitation>
concluiu que 
<taxonomicName authorityName="McAtee &amp; Malloch" authorityYear="1928" box="[262,398,1232,1255]" class="Insecta" family="Megarididae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Megarididae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Amyot &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[410,522,1231,1254]" class="Insecta" family="Canopidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Canopidae</taxonomicName>
e 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dallas" authorityYear="1851" box="[555,699,1232,1255]" class="Insecta" family="Plataspididae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Plataspididae</taxonomicName>
(esta sem representantes na região Neotropical), que têm em comum um amplo escutelo, apresentam semelhança meramente superficial. Éexclusivamente neo- tropical, com 16 espécies em um único gênero, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal. A" authorityYear="1860" class="Insecta" family="Megarididae" genus="Megaris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="404">Megaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Chave para identificação das espécies em 
<bibRefCitation author="McATEE, W. L. &amp; J. R. MALLOCH" journalOrPublisher="Proc. U. S. Natl. Mus." pageId="1" pageNumber="404" pagination="1 - 21" part="72" refId="ref3810" refString="McATEE, W. L. &amp; J. R. MALLOCH 1928. Sinopsis of pentatomid bugs of the subfamilies Megaridinae and Canopinae. Proc. U. S. Natl. Mus. 72 (25): 1 - 21." title="Sinopsis of pentatomid bugs of the subfamilies Megaridinae and Canopinae" type="journal article" year="1928">McAtee &amp; Malloch (1928)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="KORMILEV, N. A." box="[324,497,1408,1431]" journalOrPublisher="Soc. Cient. Argent." pageId="1" pageNumber="404" pagination="47 - 54" part="57" refId="ref3574" refString="KORMILEV, N. A. 1954. Una familia nueva para la fauna Argentina (Hemiptera, Megaridae) An. Soc. Cient. Argent. 57: 47 - 54." title="Una familia nueva para la fauna Argentina (Hemiptera, Megaridae) An" type="journal article" year="1954">Kormilev (1954)</bibRefCitation>
registrou 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="404">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal. A" authorityYear="1860" box="[616,699,1408,1431]" class="Insecta" family="Megarididae" genus="Megaris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Megaris</taxonomicName>
laevicollis
</emphasis>
para Corrientes. 
<bibRefCitation author="KORMILEV, N. A." box="[413,583,1438,1461]" journalOrPublisher="Acta Cient. Instit. Investig. San Miguel" pageId="1" pageNumber="404" pagination="1 - 13" part="3" refId="ref3608" refString="KORMILEV, N. A. 1956. Notas sobre Pentatomoidea neotropicales IV (Hemiptera). Acta Cient. Instit. Investig. San Miguel 3: 1 - 13." title="Notas sobre Pentatomoidea neotropicales IV (Hemiptera)" type="journal article" year="1956">Kormilev (1956)</bibRefCitation>
descreveu da Argentina 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[266,426,1467,1490]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="404">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal. A" authorityYear="1860" box="[266,349,1467,1490]" class="Insecta" family="Megarididae" genus="Megaris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Megaris</taxonomicName>
vianai
</emphasis>
procedente de Córdoba (Calamuchita, El Sauce).
</paragraph>
